2
00:00:12,437 --> 00:00:14,462
(music playing)

3
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:21,000
"God forbid that I should go to any
heaven where there are no horses."

4
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:26,000
R.B.Cunningham-Graham, 1917
letter to Theodore Roosevelt

5
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,800
Hancock County, Mississippi

6
00:01:13,630 --> 00:01:17,795
I feel so blessed when I look out
over our land, honey.

7
00:01:17,835 --> 00:01:20,895
It's so beautiful.
We are so lucky.

8
00:01:20,938 --> 00:01:24,806
- Make me a promise, babe?
- Yeah, anything.

9
00:01:24,842 --> 00:01:26,605
You'll always keep this place
in the family.

10
00:01:26,644 --> 00:01:29,112
Of course.
It's our spot.

11
00:01:29,147 --> 00:01:33,550
When I look out there, all I can see
is my blood and sweat and tears.

12
00:01:34,452 --> 00:01:37,148
This place was huge when I got it.

13
00:01:37,188 --> 00:01:40,180
- I knew what it could be, though.
- Look at it now.

14
00:01:40,224 --> 00:01:42,488
So rich, it's perfect.

15
00:01:42,527 --> 00:01:44,927
(chuckles)
Come on.

16
00:01:44,962 --> 00:01:46,725
I'm gonna race you back.

17
00:01:46,764 --> 00:01:50,063
- That is, if you're up to it, old man.
- Who you calling "old man"?

18
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:53,002
- I usually win.
- Not this time.

19
00:01:53,037 --> 00:01:54,937
If I win,
you get to do stables tonight.

20
00:01:54,972 --> 00:01:56,769
If you win, I'll do dishes.

21
00:01:56,808 --> 00:01:57,797
- Deal?
- Mm-hmm.

22
00:01:57,842 --> 00:02:01,835
How 'bout when I win, you do
the stables for a week, and the dishes.

23
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:05,300
- You're on.
- Man: Hup!

24
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Race to Redemption (2016)
Also Known As: Race to Win

25
00:03:07,778 --> 00:03:10,372
- (laughs)
- Whoa.

26
00:03:10,414 --> 00:03:13,076
Oh...

27
00:03:13,117 --> 00:03:16,086
The winner is Miss Hannah Rhodes.

28
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:18,054
Yeah, a few more yards,
I'd of had ya.

29
00:03:18,089 --> 00:03:19,386
(laughs)

30
00:03:19,423 --> 00:03:21,914
Woman on radio: All right, you two,
you proved your endurance.

31
00:03:21,959 --> 00:03:23,017
Time to wrap it up.

32
00:03:23,060 --> 00:03:24,721
These plates
aren't gonna empty themselves.

33
00:03:24,762 --> 00:03:27,458
- Wash up. Get in here.
- All right, boss lady.

34
00:03:27,498 --> 00:03:29,227
Give me five minutes, I'll be there.

35
00:03:29,267 --> 00:03:32,395
I need the five minutes,
so I don't suggest you take 'em.

36
00:03:32,436 --> 00:03:34,597
(laughs)
Well, don't be too long.

37
00:03:34,639 --> 00:03:36,072
All right.

38
00:03:40,344 --> 00:03:42,369
(horse huffs)

39
00:03:46,950 --> 00:03:48,942
(groaning)

40
00:03:55,159 --> 00:03:57,184
(music playing)

41
00:04:08,105 --> 00:04:10,130
Woman: So what did
you guys do this morning?

42
00:04:10,174 --> 00:04:13,337
Hannah: It was great.
We rode forever.

43
00:04:13,377 --> 00:04:14,844
It was fantastic.

44
00:04:16,514 --> 00:04:19,074
Where is your father?

45
00:04:19,116 --> 00:04:22,677
He said that he wanted to feed the horses
before he had lunch himself.

46
00:04:24,088 --> 00:04:25,419
Typical.

47
00:04:26,590 --> 00:04:28,855
Honey, the horses can wait.

48
00:04:28,893 --> 00:04:31,987
We can't.

49
00:04:32,029 --> 00:04:34,964
Gentry!

50
00:04:34,999 --> 00:04:37,695
Gentry.

51
00:04:40,905 --> 00:04:41,929
I'll come.

52
00:04:48,646 --> 00:04:51,171
Gentry:
I love you, son.

53
00:04:53,517 --> 00:04:57,920
Rudy, I need you to take care of
your mom and sister for me.

54
00:04:57,955 --> 00:04:59,786
And this place.

55
00:04:59,824 --> 00:05:02,691
Don't let it go, son.
It stays with us.

56
00:05:02,727 --> 00:05:04,718
Okay, Dad.

57
00:05:06,030 --> 00:05:08,157
There's something
I need you to do for me.

58
00:05:13,437 --> 00:05:15,200
Gentry?

59
00:05:15,239 --> 00:05:17,036
Gentry, baby!

60
00:05:17,074 --> 00:05:19,235
Baby, wake up.

61
00:05:19,276 --> 00:05:21,938
Wake up. Wake up.
(crying)

62
00:05:21,979 --> 00:05:24,106
He's not breathing.
He's not breathing.

63
00:05:24,148 --> 00:05:26,446
Go get help. Go!

64
00:05:26,484 --> 00:05:29,180
(sobbing)

65
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:32,189
Baby, wake up, please.

66
00:05:32,223 --> 00:05:35,090
You can't talk about it to anybody.

67
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:36,593
Ever.

68
00:05:36,627 --> 00:05:40,358
- You understand?
- I won't say a thing.

69
00:05:40,398 --> 00:05:42,491
I know.

70
00:06:36,787 --> 00:06:39,654
Woman: I think it's a bit too soon
to be packing his things, Anne.

71
00:06:40,925 --> 00:06:43,621
I don't think you're ready,

72
00:06:43,660 --> 00:06:45,652
and I don't think it's gonna
feel right for the kids.

73
00:06:47,465 --> 00:06:51,196
(inhales sharply)
What am I supposed to do now, Susie?

74
00:06:51,235 --> 00:06:54,170
Huh?
I can't afford this place.

75
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:56,002
I can't tend to it.

76
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:58,668
I told him we didn't
need this much land,

77
00:06:58,709 --> 00:07:01,906
all those horses,
but he had to have it.

78
00:07:01,946 --> 00:07:03,641
(crying)

79
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:06,149
Susie:
He did the best he could.

80
00:07:06,183 --> 00:07:07,343
You tried to tell him.

81
00:07:07,384 --> 00:07:10,046
Hey, Mom.

82
00:07:10,087 --> 00:07:11,987
You should eat something.

83
00:07:13,690 --> 00:07:14,851
Yeah.

84
00:07:20,865 --> 00:07:24,232
That is a powerful serve
you got there, Sheriff.

85
00:07:24,268 --> 00:07:26,327
You ever play professionally?

86
00:07:26,370 --> 00:07:28,861
I've just been practicing a bit.

87
00:07:28,906 --> 00:07:30,771
Yeah, well, it shows.

88
00:07:30,808 --> 00:07:34,039
Takes a confident man to master
the delicate game of tennis.

89
00:07:34,078 --> 00:07:36,774
Well, that's what they say.
Your serve.

90
00:07:40,484 --> 00:07:42,543
Oh...

91
00:07:42,586 --> 00:07:45,987
- Story of my life.
- Nah, you just pulled it.

92
00:07:46,023 --> 00:07:48,753
Uh, now, no excuses.

93
00:07:48,793 --> 00:07:52,194
Hey, uh, we appreciate the support
through the campaign.

94
00:07:52,229 --> 00:07:54,629
Look forward to making
some positive changes for the county.

95
00:07:54,665 --> 00:07:56,360
Sure, Sheriff, sure.

96
00:07:57,700 --> 00:08:01,967
Building a better community
is in everybody's best interest.

97
00:08:02,006 --> 00:08:03,337
Don't you think?

98
00:08:05,242 --> 00:08:06,903
Speaking of positive changes,

99
00:08:06,944 --> 00:08:10,539
my partners and I were thrilled to hear
about that jail you gonna build.

100
00:08:10,580 --> 00:08:12,549
We definitely vote in favor of that.

101
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:14,949
You getting at something, Darden?

102
00:08:14,985 --> 00:08:17,579
Why don't we finish this conversation
back at the house?

103
00:08:17,620 --> 00:08:19,418
Whatever you want.

104
00:08:19,456 --> 00:08:21,151
Follow me.

105
00:08:28,599 --> 00:08:31,534
Hey.

106
00:08:31,569 --> 00:08:33,935
How you holding up, banana?

107
00:08:33,970 --> 00:08:36,371
I'm okay.

108
00:08:36,407 --> 00:08:38,432
Yeah?

109
00:08:38,475 --> 00:08:40,500
(Hannah grunts)
No.

110
00:08:40,544 --> 00:08:42,705
But I will be.

111
00:08:42,746 --> 00:08:44,646
I'm really worried
about my mom and Rudy,

112
00:08:44,682 --> 00:08:48,948
and I'm trying really hard
not to completely fall apart myself.

113
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:51,481
I feel like they need me.

114
00:08:52,723 --> 00:08:54,486
Yeah.

115
00:08:54,525 --> 00:08:56,720
You know, Han, your mom and I,

116
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,921
we're been through
some really tough times.

117
00:09:00,264 --> 00:09:02,732
And we always get through 'em.

118
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:06,329
I admire your strength.

119
00:09:06,370 --> 00:09:09,362
- You need to grieve.
- I know.

120
00:09:09,406 --> 00:09:13,900
I just don't have
anything to say right now.

121
00:09:13,944 --> 00:09:15,707
Okay.

122
00:09:15,746 --> 00:09:19,147
When you're ready, I'll be waiting...

123
00:09:19,183 --> 00:09:21,344
with some rocky road
and whipped cream.

124
00:09:21,385 --> 00:09:23,785
(Hannah laughs)
I bet you will.

125
00:09:23,820 --> 00:09:27,018
- You and that sweet tooth.
- Eh.

126
00:09:27,057 --> 00:09:29,321
- I binge in moderation.
- (laughs)

127
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,351
A little.

128
00:09:31,395 --> 00:09:34,387
Well, I gotta get going.
I got a lot of things to catch up on.

129
00:09:34,430 --> 00:09:36,956
And happy that I paid attention
when Daddy was still alive,

130
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,593
or I wouldn't even know
where to start.

131
00:09:38,636 --> 00:09:40,297
Can I have a hug?

132
00:09:41,438 --> 00:09:43,838
Oh, baby.

133
00:09:44,675 --> 00:09:46,666
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

134
00:09:46,710 --> 00:09:48,678
- Gotta get going.
- Yeah.

135
00:09:48,712 --> 00:09:50,942
- Yeah.
- (clicks tongue)

136
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:55,375
So, what's your interest
in the prison, Darden?

137
00:09:55,419 --> 00:09:57,683
Darden: Assume you're gonna be
looking for a contractor.

138
00:09:57,720 --> 00:10:01,122
I'd like to be on the list
of viable candidates.

139
00:10:01,158 --> 00:10:03,888
- So, there's the catch.
- Oh, no, no catch.

140
00:10:03,928 --> 00:10:06,123
More like a suggestion.

141
00:10:06,163 --> 00:10:08,529
To our mutual benefit.

142
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:13,294
Listen, Darden.

143
00:10:13,337 --> 00:10:15,362
I know all about you
and your shenanigans.

144
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:19,866
And I've got a pretty good idea what
this county was like before I took over.

145
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:23,539
I was hired to do a job, and I'm gonna
do it to the best of my ability.

146
00:10:23,580 --> 00:10:26,174
You understand me?

147
00:10:26,216 --> 00:10:29,208
Coming in loud and clear, Sheriff.
Loud and clear.

148
00:10:30,187 --> 00:10:34,214
- Thanks for the tea.
- Oh, now, come on back.

149
00:10:34,258 --> 00:10:36,158
Play another game.
Jiminy Crickets.

150
00:10:36,193 --> 00:10:37,558
I wanna win one.

151
00:10:43,367 --> 00:10:45,562
(birds chirping)

152
00:10:45,602 --> 00:10:47,695
I took inventory last night.

153
00:10:47,738 --> 00:10:50,036
We have 12 hogs,

154
00:10:50,074 --> 00:10:52,975
42 chickens, and three cows.

155
00:10:53,010 --> 00:10:54,739
Now, we'll keep the chickens,

156
00:10:54,778 --> 00:10:58,509
but we're gonna sell the cows
and hogs to the slaughterhouse.

157
00:10:58,549 --> 00:11:00,244
What do you think, Rudy?

158
00:11:01,185 --> 00:11:03,619
Rudy, you work with
all the livestock.

159
00:11:03,654 --> 00:11:05,519
I wanna know
what you think of my plan.

160
00:11:07,558 --> 00:11:09,685
Rudy?

161
00:11:09,727 --> 00:11:11,422
Talk to me.

162
00:11:11,462 --> 00:11:13,692
Honey, say something.

163
00:11:13,730 --> 00:11:15,221
Hannah!

164
00:11:19,069 --> 00:11:21,697
So, what are you thinking, Doc?

165
00:11:21,739 --> 00:11:24,435
Well, physically,
he's perfectly healthy.

166
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:26,340
No problems there.

167
00:11:26,377 --> 00:11:28,004
He could speak if he chose to.

168
00:11:30,180 --> 00:11:32,444
So, why isn't he talking?

169
00:11:32,483 --> 00:11:35,316
Well, stress for one thing,
but in medical terms,

170
00:11:35,352 --> 00:11:38,185
we refer to it as "selective mutism".

171
00:11:38,222 --> 00:11:40,554
Hannah, can you give us
a moment alone, please?

172
00:11:47,564 --> 00:11:49,122
Doctor:
It's simple, really.

173
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:52,158
I assume this is his way of dealing
with the loss of his father.

174
00:11:53,303 --> 00:11:55,965
He's just shutdown... temporarily.

175
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:58,167
Right. Um...

176
00:11:58,208 --> 00:12:00,301
What else can we do in the meantime?

177
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:02,539
I want you to reach out
to specialist in Houston,

178
00:12:02,579 --> 00:12:03,910
try to get an appointment.

179
00:12:03,947 --> 00:12:06,745
This is not really my expertise.

180
00:12:06,784 --> 00:12:08,274
There you go.

181
00:12:08,318 --> 00:12:11,287
This doctor should be able to

182
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:15,948
ignite his speech, I can assure you,
but it will take time and money.

183
00:12:18,729 --> 00:12:20,629
Whatever it takes.

184
00:12:22,499 --> 00:12:24,490
(music playing)

185
00:12:45,322 --> 00:12:48,155
- (sobbing)
- Hannah: Mom?

186
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:52,185
It's okay.

187
00:12:53,063 --> 00:12:55,190
It's okay.

188
00:13:08,010 --> 00:13:10,002
(engine shuts off)

189
00:13:21,325 --> 00:13:23,316
(insects buzzing)

190
00:13:37,340 --> 00:13:39,036
(sighs)

191
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:47,782
Why are you banging on my door
at 7:00 in the morning?

192
00:13:47,818 --> 00:13:51,447
- You selling something?
- No, I'm not selling anything.

193
00:13:51,488 --> 00:13:53,649
But I am here on business.

194
00:13:53,690 --> 00:13:56,420
Good morning.
My name is Gregory Darden.

195
00:13:56,460 --> 00:14:00,226
Just what is your business,
Gregory Darden?

196
00:14:00,264 --> 00:14:03,893
Your husband owes me
$150,000, ma'am.

197
00:14:03,934 --> 00:14:07,426
My husband's dead, mister.

198
00:14:07,470 --> 00:14:09,735
So, I guess we're done here.

199
00:14:09,773 --> 00:14:11,764
I meant to say your late husband.

200
00:14:11,808 --> 00:14:14,072
And, no, we are not done here.

201
00:14:17,314 --> 00:14:20,681
I am very sorry for
your recent loss, Mrs. Rhodes.

202
00:14:20,717 --> 00:14:23,914
And I do apologize
for my abrupt behavior.

203
00:14:23,954 --> 00:14:27,754
In the wake of his passing,
this becomes your responsibility

204
00:14:27,790 --> 00:14:30,658
in accordance with
the community property laws

205
00:14:30,694 --> 00:14:32,286
of our great state.

206
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:34,194
Please don't do this.

207
00:14:34,230 --> 00:14:35,755
Unfortunately, when some dies,

208
00:14:35,799 --> 00:14:37,699
this wicked old world
just keeps spinning around.

209
00:14:37,734 --> 00:14:41,898
This property was collateral
against a business loan.

210
00:14:42,639 --> 00:14:45,335
Now it looks like
I'm gonna have to foreclose.

211
00:14:45,375 --> 00:14:46,865
Unless you wanna pack up right now.

212
00:14:46,910 --> 00:14:50,505
- We can call it even-steven.
- I need to call a lawyer.

213
00:14:50,547 --> 00:14:52,674
That's an excellent idea.

214
00:14:52,716 --> 00:14:56,083
Look, Mrs. Rhodes,
I'm not an unreasonable man.

215
00:14:56,119 --> 00:14:59,577
I'll even hire a realtor to help you
relocate you and the kids,

216
00:14:59,623 --> 00:15:03,389
but I am going to need
that money in 30 days.

217
00:15:04,228 --> 00:15:05,855
Otherwise, you leave me no choice

218
00:15:05,896 --> 00:15:09,423
but to return with the sheriff
and seize the property.

219
00:15:09,466 --> 00:15:10,899
By force if need be.

220
00:15:12,336 --> 00:15:14,827
Am I clear enough?

221
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:16,532
No.

222
00:15:16,573 --> 00:15:19,201
You're not clear enough.

223
00:15:19,243 --> 00:15:22,576
I can't come up with
that amount of money in 30 years.

224
00:15:23,747 --> 00:15:26,477
30 days, Mrs. Rhodes.

225
00:15:27,550 --> 00:15:30,918
You might wanna call that lawyer now.

226
00:15:31,989 --> 00:15:35,288
We have 30 days to pay Darden
or we're gonna have to leave.

227
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:39,085
What are we gonna do?

228
00:15:39,129 --> 00:15:42,690
If it weren't for Daddy, he wouldn't
have all the cash flow that he does.

229
00:15:43,667 --> 00:15:47,262
He was right not to trust him.
What a snake.

230
00:15:48,205 --> 00:15:51,902
(sighs) Well, lawyer says
there's nothing I can do.

231
00:15:51,942 --> 00:15:55,810
The judgment's valid.
He's entitled to the money Daddy owed.

232
00:15:57,347 --> 00:16:00,475
What if we race Sheba
in the barrel-racing championship?

233
00:16:00,517 --> 00:16:03,281
We can use the prize money
as down payment at least,

234
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:06,221
and we can take out a loan
on the rest.

235
00:16:06,256 --> 00:16:07,780
Seriously?

236
00:16:07,824 --> 00:16:10,315
- Hannah.
- I am serious.

237
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:12,920
We can get her in shape in time.
Donny can ride her.

238
00:16:12,963 --> 00:16:14,726
She won before, she'll win again.

239
00:16:14,765 --> 00:16:17,029
It's not a bad idea, Sue.

240
00:16:18,035 --> 00:16:19,832
None of us have come up
with anything better.

241
00:16:21,570 --> 00:16:24,734
Gent took great care of her,
and said she was his jackpot.

242
00:16:28,312 --> 00:16:31,145
Well, I hope he was right.

243
00:16:48,565 --> 00:16:49,554
(sighs)

244
00:16:53,437 --> 00:16:55,667
Dad loved you so much.

245
00:16:57,507 --> 00:17:00,499
We need you to win us
one more championship, you hear?

246
00:17:00,544 --> 00:17:02,239
Just one.

247
00:17:02,279 --> 00:17:04,076
Ain't no races left in that dud.

248
00:17:04,114 --> 00:17:05,843
Definitely no championships.

249
00:17:05,882 --> 00:17:07,816
Back for more abuse, Mr. Birch?

250
00:17:07,850 --> 00:17:10,046
Somebody's gotta
take care of the horses.

251
00:17:10,087 --> 00:17:12,248
And who else is gonna
do it at this rate?

252
00:17:12,289 --> 00:17:15,190
When you're done with Molly,
I need you to take a look at Sheba.

253
00:17:15,225 --> 00:17:18,422
We might be entering her
in some races.

254
00:17:18,462 --> 00:17:20,225
Good luck with that.

255
00:17:23,633 --> 00:17:24,622
(horse huffs)

256
00:17:38,715 --> 00:17:40,478
Whoa.

257
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:42,212
Whoa, whoa.

258
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,814
There we go.

259
00:17:46,857 --> 00:17:49,121
- Shh.
- (whickers)

260
00:17:50,260 --> 00:17:52,251
- (neighing)
- Easy now.

261
00:17:52,295 --> 00:17:56,254
- Whoa.
- Mr. Birch, I am so sorry.

262
00:18:00,003 --> 00:18:02,471
She's been kinda rowdy
since Daddy left.

263
00:18:02,506 --> 00:18:04,269
I don't get paid enough for this.

264
00:18:05,575 --> 00:18:08,135
I'll be back when you got my money.

265
00:18:19,456 --> 00:18:21,356
(engine starts)

266
00:18:26,129 --> 00:18:28,996
(whispers)
Easy, girl. Easy.

267
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,435
Donny, I know that
if you ride her, she can win.

268
00:18:33,470 --> 00:18:36,496
(Donny chuckles)
Han, this old girl's past her prime.

269
00:18:36,540 --> 00:18:38,906
Besides, your father still owes me
from last time we raced.

270
00:18:38,942 --> 00:18:41,206
Donny, my dad and I
didn't have secrets.

271
00:18:41,244 --> 00:18:44,145
Which means I know that he shaved
all the wages off your debt.

272
00:18:44,180 --> 00:18:46,376
You owe him ten grand at least.

273
00:18:46,416 --> 00:18:48,441
We had an arrangement
to get that squared away.

274
00:18:48,485 --> 00:18:51,249
So, technically, he still owed me
from our race time.

275
00:18:51,288 --> 00:18:53,085
Well, that really
isn't relevant right now.

276
00:18:53,123 --> 00:18:55,956
- Can you please just try?
- (sighs)

277
00:18:56,593 --> 00:18:58,527
- What do I get out of the deal?
- Pride.

278
00:18:58,562 --> 00:19:01,463
- (laughs)
- You can bring back the legacy

279
00:19:01,498 --> 00:19:03,159
of a man who once loved you.

280
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:06,169
And pride for yourself
for winning with an underdog.

281
00:19:08,004 --> 00:19:11,997
I would be proud and honored
to preserve your father's legacy,

282
00:19:12,042 --> 00:19:13,976
but I expect to be compensated.

283
00:19:14,010 --> 00:19:15,705
I want 10% of the winnings.

284
00:19:15,745 --> 00:19:17,235
- Five.
- Eight.

285
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:18,907
Seven.

286
00:19:19,749 --> 00:19:21,774
7.5, you got a deal.

287
00:19:21,818 --> 00:19:24,844
- Greedy deal at 7.25.
- (chuckles)

288
00:19:24,888 --> 00:19:27,186
You're your father's daughter.

289
00:19:27,224 --> 00:19:29,215
(music playing)

290
00:20:38,995 --> 00:20:41,225
Whoa, whoa.

291
00:20:41,264 --> 00:20:43,926
(grunts)
This is a waste of my time.

292
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:46,367
What's wrong?

293
00:20:46,403 --> 00:20:48,667
She gets winded every 50 feet.

294
00:20:48,705 --> 00:20:50,605
Just doesn't have the endurance.

295
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:53,404
She's just getting warmed up.
She hasn't been trained in a while.

296
00:20:53,443 --> 00:20:55,138
She'll get it.
I know she will.

297
00:20:55,178 --> 00:20:57,976
I know her competition
is gonna be more than just warm.

298
00:20:59,282 --> 00:21:02,809
Come on. She still has it in her.
I know she does.

299
00:21:05,555 --> 00:21:07,546
I'm sorry.

300
00:21:07,590 --> 00:21:09,786
Your father was a great man.

301
00:21:09,826 --> 00:21:12,317
He's gone, and that's hard, I'm sure.

302
00:21:12,362 --> 00:21:14,830
But you're holding on to something
that doesn't exist anymore.

303
00:21:14,864 --> 00:21:17,424
This horse is not a winner.

304
00:21:17,467 --> 00:21:19,935
And she's never gonna be
a winner ever again, Hannah.

305
00:21:20,937 --> 00:21:23,167
You need to find another way
to come up with that money.

306
00:21:23,206 --> 00:21:25,265
'Cause this is not gonna be
a good return on your investment.

307
00:21:25,308 --> 00:21:27,435
I promise.

308
00:21:28,578 --> 00:21:31,012
So, you're just quitting?

309
00:21:31,047 --> 00:21:33,607
One frustrating day
and you're just done?

310
00:21:33,650 --> 00:21:36,050
My father loved you.

311
00:21:36,086 --> 00:21:39,578
He taught you everything you know
and he gave you your big break.

312
00:21:39,623 --> 00:21:42,786
Honor his memory
and just try harder.

313
00:21:42,826 --> 00:21:44,555
Donny!

314
00:21:45,762 --> 00:21:47,559
(softly)
You're all we have.

315
00:21:50,867 --> 00:21:53,062
Well, hello.

316
00:21:53,103 --> 00:21:54,900
I didn't know you'd be here.

317
00:21:56,806 --> 00:22:00,367
Dr. Smith asked when the horses
last had wormer.

318
00:22:00,410 --> 00:22:02,275
I don't know.

319
00:22:03,279 --> 00:22:06,544
- When did the farrier come last?
- I don't know.

320
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:09,210
Well, what do you know?

321
00:22:11,287 --> 00:22:14,154
That my husband's gone.

322
00:22:16,826 --> 00:22:18,851
I can't do it without him.

323
00:22:21,297 --> 00:22:24,596
- I'm all alone.
- You have me.

324
00:22:24,634 --> 00:22:26,966
And you are stuck with me.

325
00:22:27,003 --> 00:22:28,561
Whether you like it or not.

326
00:22:31,408 --> 00:22:33,308
They need you, Anne.

327
00:22:35,310 --> 00:22:37,302
(music playing)

328
00:23:14,650 --> 00:23:16,346
This is it.

329
00:23:19,322 --> 00:23:21,313
I wanna put the deck
out here somewhere.

330
00:23:21,357 --> 00:23:23,416
Kinda surround the pool, you know?

331
00:23:23,460 --> 00:23:27,897
I want an entertainment area to grilling.
I like to grill, a lot.

332
00:23:29,299 --> 00:23:31,290
I can make some better use
of them stables.

333
00:23:31,334 --> 00:23:33,802
Maybe a warehouse, boat or RV garage?

334
00:23:33,837 --> 00:23:35,668
Perfect.

335
00:23:35,705 --> 00:23:37,570
Tennis court's out there
somewhere, of course.

336
00:23:37,607 --> 00:23:39,871
Me and the sheriff like to play.

337
00:23:39,909 --> 00:23:44,107
Man, I have been waiting
to get my hands on this property.

338
00:23:44,147 --> 00:23:47,014
I am going to use this place.

339
00:23:47,050 --> 00:23:49,712
- Maybe a nine-hole golf course.
- You think there's room?

340
00:23:49,753 --> 00:23:52,415
Sure. All you gotta do is mow down
some of these fields.

341
00:23:52,455 --> 00:23:56,152
Well, draw it up. More activities
the merrier, don't you think?

342
00:23:56,192 --> 00:24:00,185
What are you doing here?
Get off my property!

343
00:24:01,030 --> 00:24:03,726
Safe to say,
I already own it, Mrs. Rhodes.

344
00:24:03,767 --> 00:24:05,325
Just a matter of time.

345
00:24:06,436 --> 00:24:08,495
Hey! Watch it!

346
00:24:08,538 --> 00:24:10,438
These are imported-handmade.

347
00:24:10,473 --> 00:24:14,102
You need to leave right now,
before I get my rifle.

348
00:24:15,478 --> 00:24:18,276
There's no need for that, Mrs. Rhodes.

349
00:24:18,314 --> 00:24:19,781
Hannah!

350
00:24:20,984 --> 00:24:22,645
Hannah: Yeah, Mom?

351
00:24:24,087 --> 00:24:26,521
I am putting y'all out.
All of ya.

352
00:24:26,556 --> 00:24:28,956
- Get my 30/30.
- You know that, right?

353
00:24:28,992 --> 00:24:32,553
(sighs) Come on.
Let's let the chickens have their day.

354
00:24:41,670 --> 00:24:43,935
(breathing heavily)

355
00:24:47,710 --> 00:24:49,701
Brass is worth money.

356
00:24:49,746 --> 00:24:53,045
Gotta liquidate everything we have
if we're gonna make a dent in that debt.

357
00:24:53,082 --> 00:24:56,540
You're gonna need a lot more brass
if you're gonna pay back Darden.

358
00:25:00,023 --> 00:25:02,651
Um, Donny quit today.

359
00:25:02,692 --> 00:25:04,683
What?

360
00:25:04,727 --> 00:25:07,195
So, the race won't be an option
for us anymore.

361
00:25:16,573 --> 00:25:18,837
Hannah...

362
00:25:18,875 --> 00:25:20,399
why don't you race?

363
00:25:20,443 --> 00:25:23,742
Daddy trained you.
You guys won two races.

364
00:25:23,780 --> 00:25:25,680
- I'm not ready.
- (sighs)

365
00:25:25,715 --> 00:25:27,842
I'm never racing again.

366
00:25:27,884 --> 00:25:29,545
I can't without Dad.

367
00:25:30,787 --> 00:25:35,190
Daddy would never want you to give up
on something you love so much.

368
00:25:35,925 --> 00:25:38,257
- You have to do it.
- No, I don't.

369
00:25:39,863 --> 00:25:42,661
Then what can I do?

370
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:45,562
I'm not ready.

371
00:26:06,356 --> 00:26:08,153
Daddy...

372
00:26:09,259 --> 00:26:11,887
we need your help.

373
00:26:11,928 --> 00:26:13,259
Everything's falling apart,

374
00:26:13,296 --> 00:26:15,628
and I don't know
how much more Mama can take.

375
00:26:15,665 --> 00:26:18,099
And Rudy won't even talk to us.

376
00:26:20,203 --> 00:26:22,262
Please, Daddy, help us.

377
00:26:26,276 --> 00:26:28,471
Waste.

378
00:26:30,013 --> 00:26:31,674
(horse neighs)

379
00:26:31,714 --> 00:26:35,309
¶ He's thought about
¶ making amends

380
00:26:35,350 --> 00:26:38,377
¶ But he's closed the barn door
¶ way too late

381
00:26:38,420 --> 00:26:41,185
¶ Those folks
¶ are no longer his friends

382
00:26:42,592 --> 00:26:46,119
¶ Yeah, he keeps selling out,
¶ then he tries to buy back

383
00:26:46,162 --> 00:26:48,722
¶ When he wins some money
¶ at the dog track...

384
00:26:48,765 --> 00:26:53,259
Four in a row, old man.
You sure you wanna keep this up?

385
00:26:53,303 --> 00:26:55,828
I almost feel bad
taking this money from you.

386
00:26:57,407 --> 00:26:59,671
It's a Christmas present from my wife.

387
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:07,308
Seriously gonna drop
your marital timepiece

388
00:27:07,350 --> 00:27:09,818
on a game of nine-ball?

389
00:27:09,852 --> 00:27:12,320
I don't have any way
to win my money back.

390
00:27:12,355 --> 00:27:14,016
Okay.

391
00:27:14,057 --> 00:27:16,389
Me, too.
Rack 'em, old man.

392
00:27:16,426 --> 00:27:18,553
That won't be necessary.

393
00:27:20,063 --> 00:27:23,032
Take this...

394
00:27:23,066 --> 00:27:24,727
and take a hike.

395
00:27:27,437 --> 00:27:29,871
- Christmas come early.
- Move. Scram.

396
00:27:29,906 --> 00:27:32,397
Vamoose.
(chuckling)

397
00:27:34,978 --> 00:27:37,071
How much he take you for?

398
00:27:37,113 --> 00:27:39,206
- It doesn't matter.
- Oh, now, come on.

399
00:27:39,248 --> 00:27:42,183
What's the fun of being rich
if you can't spread the wealth around?

400
00:27:43,386 --> 00:27:45,183
I don't want your money.

401
00:27:45,220 --> 00:27:48,247
Look, I know
you haven't been paid out

402
00:27:48,290 --> 00:27:50,623
the Rhode's place
since Gentry passed.

403
00:27:50,660 --> 00:27:52,560
Let me help you with that.

404
00:27:53,496 --> 00:27:56,988
I know those mouths back at the house
are wide open and waiting.

405
00:27:57,033 --> 00:27:59,558
Like little birds.
(chuckles)

406
00:28:00,503 --> 00:28:03,097
What do you think?
Let me buy you a drink.

407
00:28:04,807 --> 00:28:06,502
All right.

408
00:28:06,542 --> 00:28:08,533
- Just one drink.
- All right.

409
00:28:08,578 --> 00:28:10,705
- That's the spirit.
- (knocks on table)

410
00:28:34,904 --> 00:28:37,304
Where have you been?
I've been freaking out.

411
00:28:48,317 --> 00:28:51,115
"Your father was a good man.
I raised this horse to run.

412
00:28:51,154 --> 00:28:54,385
His name is Atonement.
He's my gift to you.

413
00:28:54,424 --> 00:28:56,221
Race him and you will win.

414
00:28:56,259 --> 00:29:00,127
I hope to visit soon.
Sincerely, your concerned friend".

415
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:05,963
Is this a joke?

416
00:29:06,002 --> 00:29:08,470
There's no way this is real.

417
00:29:09,839 --> 00:29:11,807
(sighs) Rudy, help me
get this horse to the barn.

418
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:14,207
We have to get him hydrated
before he falls over.

419
00:29:14,243 --> 00:29:16,711
- Rudy: Wait.
- Rudy!

420
00:29:19,082 --> 00:29:21,073
Come on, Rudy, say it.

421
00:29:22,485 --> 00:29:25,716
Rudy, if you have something
to say just say it.

422
00:29:28,357 --> 00:29:31,224
You should race... for Dad.

423
00:29:42,605 --> 00:29:44,596
I'll do it.

424
00:29:44,640 --> 00:29:46,505
I'll race.

425
00:29:48,710 --> 00:29:50,076
Come on.

426
00:29:56,486 --> 00:29:58,477
(music playing)

427
00:32:29,639 --> 00:32:31,129
Everything okay?

428
00:32:32,842 --> 00:32:34,275
Yep, I'm fine.

429
00:32:36,245 --> 00:32:38,679
You're doing a great job.

430
00:32:38,714 --> 00:32:41,615
You aren't ready to quit on me,
are ya?

431
00:32:44,420 --> 00:32:47,150
You know, sometimes I feel like
I'm the adult in this relationship.

432
00:32:49,292 --> 00:32:51,783
- What do you mean?
- (sighs)

433
00:32:51,827 --> 00:32:53,852
I mean I feel like I'm the one
carrying all the weight,

434
00:32:53,896 --> 00:32:56,626
and you expect me to save everyone.

435
00:32:56,666 --> 00:32:58,964
Bail us out of this mess.

436
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,935
Pay back for Daddy's mistakes.

437
00:33:00,970 --> 00:33:04,337
However you wanna look at it,
I can't stand the pressure, Mom.

438
00:33:05,207 --> 00:33:06,731
Hannah.

439
00:33:08,610 --> 00:33:11,341
It's not fair,
and I don't even think I can do it.

440
00:33:12,515 --> 00:33:13,948
Hannah!

441
00:33:22,258 --> 00:33:23,919
Hannah: It's gonna be hard
to leave this place.

442
00:33:23,959 --> 00:33:27,156
It's like losing Dad all over again.

443
00:33:27,196 --> 00:33:29,323
Except, I haven't even recovered
from the first time.

444
00:33:29,365 --> 00:33:32,095
We're not going anywhere.

445
00:33:32,134 --> 00:33:34,602
You have to have more faith
than that, Han.

446
00:33:35,270 --> 00:33:37,831
We're out of time.
We're completely out of options.

447
00:33:37,873 --> 00:33:39,864
We're not gonna figure it out.

448
00:33:41,210 --> 00:33:45,271
Well, I remember when
your dad took on this ranch.

449
00:33:45,314 --> 00:33:48,010
It was like an impossible task.

450
00:33:48,050 --> 00:33:50,143
No one believed
that he could do it.

451
00:33:50,186 --> 00:33:52,518
He had a vision.

452
00:33:52,555 --> 00:33:55,581
And we take view.

453
00:33:55,624 --> 00:33:57,615
You get what I'm saying?

454
00:33:57,660 --> 00:34:00,595
Yeah. Yeah,
I get what you're saying.

455
00:34:01,564 --> 00:34:03,225
Win that race...

456
00:34:03,265 --> 00:34:05,563
and honor him.

457
00:34:08,437 --> 00:34:10,428
(music playing)

458
00:34:36,665 --> 00:34:39,259
What are you so down for, baby girl?

459
00:34:40,503 --> 00:34:42,733
It's just a test of your strength.

460
00:34:42,772 --> 00:34:44,967
Don't let it break you.

461
00:34:46,175 --> 00:34:48,336
I love you all very much.

462
00:34:50,413 --> 00:34:52,142
I miss you, Daddy.

463
00:35:03,459 --> 00:35:04,483
(cheering and applause)

464
00:35:04,527 --> 00:35:06,620
Announcer: Up next,
we have veteran Charlie East

465
00:35:06,662 --> 00:35:09,222
of Hancock County riding Blue Steel.

466
00:35:27,817 --> 00:35:31,309
That's 15.3 for Charlie East
of Hancock County.

467
00:35:34,523 --> 00:35:36,855
15.3, I can't even
come close to that.

468
00:35:36,892 --> 00:35:39,725
Baby, it's just the qualifying race.

469
00:35:39,762 --> 00:35:42,526
If it doesn't work out today,
you still have another shot.

470
00:35:42,565 --> 00:35:45,796
Your daddy taught you
everything you need to know.

471
00:35:45,835 --> 00:35:48,827
He believed in you.

472
00:35:48,870 --> 00:35:50,964
I believe in you.

473
00:35:51,006 --> 00:35:52,701
You can do this.

474
00:35:52,740 --> 00:35:56,142
Okay. Okay.
I'm ready.

475
00:35:56,178 --> 00:35:59,545
Remember, if you feel him slowing down,
give him a good nudge.

476
00:35:59,582 --> 00:36:01,413
You're in control, okay?

477
00:36:01,450 --> 00:36:03,714
You can do this.

478
00:36:03,752 --> 00:36:05,583
Okay.

479
00:36:05,620 --> 00:36:07,145
That's my girl.

480
00:36:07,189 --> 00:36:09,453
- Okay.
- Announcer: Up next, we have newcomer

481
00:36:09,492 --> 00:36:11,824
Hannah Rhodes riding Atonement.

482
00:36:17,099 --> 00:36:20,262
It's not too late to back out, Han.
You don't have to do this.

483
00:36:20,302 --> 00:36:23,635
I wanna do it, Daddy.
I wanna race.

484
00:36:24,406 --> 00:36:26,670
Well, I've never been
more proud of you.

485
00:36:27,610 --> 00:36:29,168
Thanks, Dad.

486
00:36:29,210 --> 00:36:33,113
I just wish I was someone that
you could've been more proud of.

487
00:36:33,148 --> 00:36:36,276
Nobody's perfect, but in my eyes,
you were as close as it gets.

488
00:36:36,318 --> 00:36:38,718
I'm so proud to be your daughter.

489
00:36:40,990 --> 00:36:44,357
So grown up.
When did that happen?

490
00:36:46,228 --> 00:36:48,162
All right.

491
00:36:49,230 --> 00:36:50,892
You go get 'em, baby girl.

492
00:36:50,933 --> 00:36:53,902
- I'll be right there with you.
- (exhales sharply)

493
00:36:53,936 --> 00:36:55,801
I won't let you down, old man.

494
00:36:55,838 --> 00:36:58,864
I won't let you down either.

495
00:36:58,908 --> 00:37:00,899
(cheering and applause)

496
00:37:25,634 --> 00:37:28,501
Announcer:
That's a 14.9 from Hannah Rhodes.

497
00:37:28,537 --> 00:37:31,904
That run qualifies her for
the 4-Friends championship next week.

498
00:37:31,940 --> 00:37:34,000
- Congratulations, Hannah, and Atonement.
- I knew you could do it!

499
00:37:34,043 --> 00:37:35,908
I knew you could do it.

500
00:37:35,945 --> 00:37:37,776
That was amazing.

501
00:37:39,448 --> 00:37:41,439
(music playing)

502
00:38:13,482 --> 00:38:14,915
Uh, hi.

503
00:38:14,950 --> 00:38:17,282
I have a delivery
for Miss Hannah Rhodes.

504
00:38:17,319 --> 00:38:19,082
You're looking at her.

505
00:38:20,022 --> 00:38:22,957
Here you go, and sign here, please.

506
00:38:23,492 --> 00:38:25,357
Hold that.

507
00:38:27,196 --> 00:38:30,563
- Thanks.
- Oh! My riding boots.

508
