(music playing on radio)

761
00:55:08,930 --> 00:55:11,490
Oh, there you are, Jeffery.

762
00:55:11,532 --> 00:55:14,000
Nicely done, Jeffery, nicely done.

763
00:55:14,035 --> 00:55:17,801
- My money.
- What money?

764
00:55:17,839 --> 00:55:21,673
You said that if I did that thing for you,
you would give me more money.

765
00:55:22,744 --> 00:55:26,737
- Did I say that?
- Yeah, you did, and I want my money.

766
00:55:26,780 --> 00:55:28,806
I think you misunderstood
our arrangement.

767
00:55:28,850 --> 00:55:30,545
I said I would clear your debt.

768
00:55:30,585 --> 00:55:33,179
I never said I would
pay you for anything.

769
00:55:33,220 --> 00:55:36,088
Hey, you better take it
down a notch, Jeffery!

770
00:55:36,124 --> 00:55:38,684
You best tread
very lightly right now.

771
00:55:38,726 --> 00:55:41,627
Otherwise, you are gonna
ruin my celebration.

772
00:55:41,663 --> 00:55:44,063
You don't wanna ruin my celebration,
do you, Jeffery?

773
00:55:44,098 --> 00:55:46,896
Because that would
make me very angry.

774
00:55:46,934 --> 00:55:50,529
And if I became angry, I would
have to find a place to put that anger.

775
00:55:50,570 --> 00:55:52,061
And there you are.

776
00:55:52,106 --> 00:55:54,233
Right there in front of me.

777
00:55:54,275 --> 00:55:56,573
So...

778
00:55:56,610 --> 00:55:58,602
we done here?

779
00:56:03,317 --> 00:56:05,581
Where is that little girl?

780
00:56:05,620 --> 00:56:07,918
I like that little girl.

781
00:56:11,626 --> 00:56:13,617
(music playing)

782
00:56:20,234 --> 00:56:25,103
¶ I've never been afraid

783
00:56:25,139 --> 00:56:28,700
¶ Of sinking like a stone

784
00:56:34,849 --> 00:56:39,377
¶ Holding on to everything

785
00:56:40,220 --> 00:56:42,951
¶ Jumping in alone

786
00:56:48,262 --> 00:56:52,221
¶ It's like I rush to the bottom

787
00:56:52,266 --> 00:56:56,168
¶ Always craving the deep end

788
00:56:56,204 --> 00:56:59,002
¶ That feeling of falling

789
00:56:59,040 --> 00:57:03,067
¶ Yeah, that feeling of sinking

790
00:57:03,110 --> 00:57:06,239
¶ I am so heavy

791
00:57:06,280 --> 00:57:11,741
¶ When will I just learn to float?

792
00:57:24,999 --> 00:57:26,591
Bye now, girl.

793
00:57:27,835 --> 00:57:30,565
You were always his favorite.

794
00:57:33,040 --> 00:57:34,735
It's just you and me now.

795
00:57:38,746 --> 00:57:40,839
Hannah:
So this is plan B?

796
00:57:40,882 --> 00:57:42,747
Just leaving.

797
00:57:44,519 --> 00:57:46,214
Look at the bright side.

798
00:57:46,254 --> 00:57:50,190
No more maintaining
all this land, this big house.

799
00:57:50,224 --> 00:57:53,455
No more picking up poop for me.

800
00:57:53,494 --> 00:57:55,485
Exactly.

801
00:57:57,398 --> 00:58:01,596
Well, maybe we'll move
to a high-rise in the city.

802
00:58:04,839 --> 00:58:06,739
- The city?
- What do you think?

803
00:58:06,774 --> 00:58:09,004
I can't just park my horse
at a parking meter.

804
00:58:09,043 --> 00:58:10,601
Okay.

805
00:58:12,480 --> 00:58:14,141
Maybe not the city.

806
00:58:17,218 --> 00:58:19,243
I really am sorry, Hannah.

807
00:58:19,287 --> 00:58:21,881
I really am.

808
00:58:21,923 --> 00:58:23,515
For what?

809
00:58:23,558 --> 00:58:26,823
I should never have
put so much pressure on you.

810
00:58:26,860 --> 00:58:28,954
It was never your problem to solve.

811
00:58:29,764 --> 00:58:32,961
It was wrong of me
to burden you with it all.

812
00:58:33,000 --> 00:58:35,662
I like doing all that stuff.

813
00:58:35,703 --> 00:58:39,537
It makes me feel like
I'm filling Daddy's shoes.

814
00:58:39,574 --> 00:58:42,566
Besides, Dad always told me
I was his toughest cowgirl.

815
00:58:44,010 --> 00:58:46,070
Yeah, that sounds like Daddy.

816
00:58:46,113 --> 00:58:48,172
(chuckles)

817
00:58:48,216 --> 00:58:49,945
Now pack.

818
00:58:49,984 --> 00:58:53,044
We have to get this done
so we can just move on.

819
00:58:58,426 --> 00:59:00,826
Promise me one thing, Hannah.

820
00:59:00,862 --> 00:59:02,022
What?

821
00:59:02,063 --> 00:59:04,395
That you just be a kid.

822
00:59:04,432 --> 00:59:07,629
You've always been so grown up.

823
00:59:07,668 --> 00:59:09,693
I want you to just focus on yourself.

824
00:59:09,737 --> 00:59:11,796
Okay?
No more training.

825
00:59:11,839 --> 00:59:13,864
No more excessive chores.

826
00:59:13,908 --> 00:59:15,739
No parenting your brother.

827
00:59:17,945 --> 00:59:19,640
Me, for that matter.

828
00:59:20,815 --> 00:59:23,613
Let that be a change you make.

829
00:59:24,952 --> 00:59:27,386
- Meet some kids your own age.
- (sighs)

830
00:59:27,420 --> 00:59:29,651
Meet a boy.

831
00:59:29,690 --> 00:59:31,624
- (laughs)
- You need that.

832
00:59:31,659 --> 00:59:34,560
I'm really okay, Mom.

833
00:59:34,595 --> 00:59:36,688
You are too much, girl.

834
00:59:38,566 --> 00:59:40,397
All right.

835
00:59:54,215 --> 00:59:56,206
(whickering)

836
01:00:01,355 --> 01:00:03,289
Hey, girl.

837
01:00:04,558 --> 01:00:06,116
Hi.

838
01:00:16,637 --> 01:00:18,195
It's coming, girl.

839
01:00:26,213 --> 01:00:28,511
Mom and Rudy, hurry up.
It's coming right now.

840
01:00:28,549 --> 01:00:30,176
Hurry.

841
01:00:33,620 --> 01:00:35,851
He's got you pretty
stressed out today, huh?

842
01:00:37,658 --> 01:00:39,523
You need something a little stronger?

843
01:00:42,063 --> 01:00:43,758
Pour me something, Teddy.

844
01:00:44,198 --> 01:00:47,531
¶ Well, the whippoorwill

845
01:00:47,568 --> 01:00:51,129
¶ Is a desperate bird

846
01:00:51,172 --> 01:00:54,266
¶ She steals the sunshine...

847
01:00:54,308 --> 01:00:56,003
You could've said no.

848
01:00:56,043 --> 01:00:58,341
Said no to what?

849
01:00:58,379 --> 01:01:01,712
Come on, Jeff.
I saw you talking to Darden.

850
01:01:01,749 --> 01:01:03,717
I heard what he talked you into.

851
01:01:10,624 --> 01:01:12,285
I needed the money.

852
01:01:12,326 --> 01:01:15,261
You needed money, Jeff?

853
01:01:15,296 --> 01:01:18,163
We all need money.

854
01:01:21,235 --> 01:01:23,226
There are more honest ways
to earn a buck.

855
01:01:28,109 --> 01:01:30,168
There are good people, Jeff.

856
01:01:30,210 --> 01:01:32,907
This is your chance
to be one of 'em.

857
01:01:36,450 --> 01:01:38,247
Do the right thing.

858
01:01:39,520 --> 01:01:41,488
Or I will.

859
01:01:45,459 --> 01:01:49,395
¶ When the highway

860
01:01:49,430 --> 01:01:51,864
¶ Is your friend
(sighs)

861
01:01:55,436 --> 01:01:57,734
How.. how is she?

862
01:01:57,772 --> 01:02:00,366
Is the baby okay?

863
01:02:00,408 --> 01:02:02,569
She's just fine.

864
01:02:02,610 --> 01:02:04,737
It's a boy.

865
01:02:06,880 --> 01:02:08,610
What should we name him?

866
01:02:08,649 --> 01:02:11,117
- Redemption.
- (horse huffs)

867
01:02:11,152 --> 01:02:13,552
I think that's a fine name, Hannah.

868
01:02:18,259 --> 01:02:19,954
Oh, I'll get your money.

869
01:02:19,994 --> 01:02:23,225
Oh, not necessary.
On the house.

870
01:02:23,264 --> 01:02:27,963
My thank you to Gent and to you
for always taking such good care of me.

871
01:02:28,002 --> 01:02:29,799
Oh, thank you.

872
01:02:30,670 --> 01:02:33,162
Oh, we'll miss times like these.

873
01:02:33,207 --> 01:02:35,141
You've always been so wonderful.

874
01:02:35,176 --> 01:02:37,974
We have so many great memories
of you and these horses.

875
01:02:38,012 --> 01:02:40,378
Well, we need to make sure
we get this colt on medication

876
01:02:40,414 --> 01:02:42,644
to make sure he gets a good start.

877
01:02:42,683 --> 01:02:45,208
- Use your money for that.
- Thank you.

878
01:02:58,566 --> 01:03:01,433
This is your time now, son.

879
01:03:02,436 --> 01:03:06,930
I'm sorry you had to grow up so fast,
but I know you're gonna do well.

880
01:03:06,974 --> 01:03:10,068
I need you to take care of
your mom and my baby girl.

881
01:03:11,612 --> 01:03:13,944
I love you.

882
01:03:13,980 --> 01:03:16,176
Always.

883
01:03:23,457 --> 01:03:25,220
Hannah:
We can't keep going.

884
01:03:25,259 --> 01:03:28,319
We don't have any more time.
Darden's taken everything away.

885
01:03:28,362 --> 01:03:32,628
Well, our fate
hasn't been sealed yet.

886
01:03:33,567 --> 01:03:35,398
Anything could happen.

887
01:03:40,508 --> 01:03:42,169
Anything.

888
01:03:43,077 --> 01:03:47,776
Well, is that a smile?

889
01:03:47,815 --> 01:03:50,215
- Maybe.
- Oh...

890
01:03:50,250 --> 01:03:52,310
- I like smiles.
- (giggling)

891
01:04:09,036 --> 01:04:12,699
- Where's the colt?
- It's in the barn.

892
01:04:12,740 --> 01:04:14,469
Well, let's go take a look.

893
01:04:30,090 --> 01:04:32,149
I was thinking about making

894
01:04:32,193 --> 01:04:36,254
some of my famous
blueberry pancakes for you two.

895
01:04:36,897 --> 01:04:39,092
I mean, if.. if you want me to.

896
01:04:39,133 --> 01:04:41,829
- Really?
- Yes.

897
01:04:43,537 --> 01:04:45,596
- All right.
- (giggling)

898
01:04:45,639 --> 01:04:48,335
- I'm gonna go get some blueberries and...
- (engine idling, horn honks)

899
01:04:48,375 --> 01:04:51,572
- Do you hear that?
- Is that Darden?

900
01:04:52,746 --> 01:04:54,941
Better not be Darden.

901
01:04:54,982 --> 01:04:56,574
It didn't look like Darden.

902
01:05:14,668 --> 01:05:16,659
- Hey there.
- (horse huffs)

903
01:05:17,870 --> 01:05:21,068
You're a beautiful boy.

904
01:05:21,108 --> 01:05:23,941
You gonna make one heck of
a racehorse someday.

905
01:05:25,279 --> 01:05:26,712
Yes, you will.

906
01:05:28,649 --> 01:05:30,310
Yes, you will.

907
01:05:32,987 --> 01:05:35,285
That is one good-looking horse,
my friend.

908
01:05:38,459 --> 01:05:40,552
- Morning, ladies.
- Anne: Who might you be?

909
01:05:40,594 --> 01:05:44,052
You one of Darden's goons?
We're almost done packing.

910
01:05:44,098 --> 01:05:45,395
Darden?

911
01:05:45,432 --> 01:05:48,299
I wouldn't be caught dead in
the same room with a crook like Darden.

912
01:05:48,335 --> 01:05:49,927
My name's Carter.

913
01:05:51,905 --> 01:05:53,896
Well, what are you doing here, Carter?

914
01:05:53,940 --> 01:05:56,501
And how does my son
know you and I don't?

915
01:05:56,543 --> 01:05:58,374
I beg your pardon, ladies.

916
01:05:58,412 --> 01:06:00,539
I mean you no harm.

917
01:06:00,580 --> 01:06:02,879
I just came to check on
my colt over there.

918
01:06:02,916 --> 01:06:05,612
Now, let me
tell you something, mister.

919
01:06:05,653 --> 01:06:07,553
- Carter.
- Carter.

920
01:06:07,588 --> 01:06:09,351
We've already lost our ranch.

921
01:06:09,390 --> 01:06:11,858
- Miss...
- Susie.

922
01:06:11,892 --> 01:06:14,725
Susie, I don't come here emptyhanded.

923
01:06:14,762 --> 01:06:16,024
Nor am I here to collect a debt,

924
01:06:16,063 --> 01:06:19,464
like everybody else
who walks onto this property.

925
01:06:19,500 --> 01:06:22,469
What I intend to do
is to write y'all a big ol' check,

926
01:06:22,503 --> 01:06:24,971
and in exchange,
you will relinquish to me

927
01:06:25,005 --> 01:06:27,838
that fine racing specimen
in the stall over there.

928
01:06:27,875 --> 01:06:29,638
What are you talking about?

929
01:06:29,677 --> 01:06:33,010
Gentry bred his mare to a stallion

930
01:06:33,047 --> 01:06:35,743
- ..named Astounding Day.
- No way.

931
01:06:35,783 --> 01:06:39,219
You mean the champion
thoroughbred Astounding Day?

932
01:06:39,253 --> 01:06:40,720
The very same.

933
01:06:40,754 --> 01:06:44,315
I received an invitation
to buy the foal at birth.

934
01:06:44,358 --> 01:06:47,327
- What?
- That's right.

935
01:06:47,360 --> 01:06:51,320
Rudy over there gave me notice,
so I'm here to claim my door prize.

936
01:06:52,032 --> 01:06:53,556
I...

937
01:06:53,600 --> 01:06:55,397
Rudy gave you notice?

938
01:06:59,440 --> 01:07:04,309
This is a signed agreement
between Gentry and myself.

939
01:07:04,345 --> 01:07:07,508
Both our attorneys were present
during the negotiations.

940
01:07:07,548 --> 01:07:10,847
Our agreement took place
long before Gentry's death,

941
01:07:10,884 --> 01:07:14,980
and so it predates
any claim to ownership by Darden.

942
01:07:16,290 --> 01:07:19,919
- Mr. Carter, are you serious?
- I'm serious, little lady.

943
01:07:19,960 --> 01:07:23,487
Now, if y'all don't mind, I'd like to
give you a check and be on my way.

944
01:07:23,530 --> 01:07:27,296
I do want my vet to come
and take a look at the colt immediately.

945
01:07:27,334 --> 01:07:29,199
If y'all don't mind.

946
01:07:42,282 --> 01:07:45,274
This is a fabulous opportunity
for Redemption.

947
01:07:45,319 --> 01:07:46,946
How much did you guys agree on?

948
01:07:46,987 --> 01:07:51,686
Well, I'm gonna shave off
his gambling debts from the price.

949
01:07:51,725 --> 01:07:56,595
After deducting those bets,
I'm gonna owe you $250,000.

950
01:07:56,630 --> 01:07:59,064
What?

951
01:07:59,099 --> 01:08:00,794
250,000?

952
01:08:00,834 --> 01:08:02,802
Is that what you just said?

953
01:08:02,836 --> 01:08:07,034
Yes, he did, and it's too late
to take it back now.

954
01:08:09,343 --> 01:08:12,710
Sir, you just bought yourself
a racing horse.

955
01:08:21,054 --> 01:08:24,615
Um, I'll go grab your paperwork.

956
01:08:24,658 --> 01:08:26,819
- We had a vet..
- We'll handle the paperwork later on.

957
01:08:26,860 --> 01:08:29,522
Rudy, have a good one, sir.

958
01:08:29,563 --> 01:08:32,930
Wait, what time does the bank close?
Is today Friday or Saturday?

959
01:08:32,966 --> 01:08:35,560
- Can we cash this check right now?
- I don't see why not.

960
01:08:35,602 --> 01:08:37,467
I think the bank's open
a few more hours.

961
01:08:37,504 --> 01:08:39,165
Oh!

962
01:08:40,140 --> 01:08:42,267
- Oh! (screams)
- This can't be happening.

963
01:08:42,309 --> 01:08:43,901
(cheering)

964
01:08:43,944 --> 01:08:46,640
Oh, my God!

965
01:08:46,680 --> 01:08:48,671
(screaming)

966
01:09:15,075 --> 01:09:18,567
Hello, Darden.
It's a pleasure to see you.

967
01:09:18,612 --> 01:09:21,103
Well, I'm glad to see

968
01:09:21,148 --> 01:09:23,048
you've touched base with reality.

969
01:09:23,083 --> 01:09:24,573
At last.

970
01:09:24,618 --> 01:09:27,143
Y'all packed up?
Ready to go?

971
01:09:27,187 --> 01:09:29,485
Yeah, I packed.

972
01:09:29,523 --> 01:09:32,083
We were all packed.

973
01:09:32,125 --> 01:09:34,787
But then we unpacked.

974
01:09:34,828 --> 01:09:36,887
So...

975
01:09:38,532 --> 01:09:40,397
Why on earth would you do that?

976
01:09:40,434 --> 01:09:42,493
We found a way to pay you.

977
01:09:45,038 --> 01:09:48,371
- We got your money.
- All your money.

978
01:09:48,408 --> 01:09:50,501
Plus interest.

979
01:09:50,544 --> 01:09:52,671
I assume you'll be satisfied now.

980
01:09:53,680 --> 01:09:56,274
You know, I think it's time that
you and your fan club get going.

981
01:09:57,150 --> 01:10:00,586
Otherwise, we'll have to forcibly
remove you from the property.

982
01:10:00,620 --> 01:10:03,317
Get off our property, Darden.

983
01:10:04,790 --> 01:10:07,885
I'll bet you this thing ain't worth
the paper it's printed on.

984
01:10:09,463 --> 01:10:11,624
Y'all think you can
play me for a fool?

985
01:10:11,665 --> 01:10:14,793
(laughs) We already know
you're a fool, Darden.

986
01:10:14,835 --> 01:10:16,735
But the check is good.

987
01:10:16,770 --> 01:10:19,068
Call the bank.
They're open till four.

988
01:10:19,106 --> 01:10:21,404
Call the bank?
Call the bank.

989
01:10:21,440 --> 01:10:23,466
I'm gonna call the police.
That's who I'm gonna call.

990
01:10:23,510 --> 01:10:27,139
I am serious.
You all need to think about this.

991
01:10:27,180 --> 01:10:29,910
Looks like somebody
already made that call.

992
01:10:29,950 --> 01:10:31,941
(laughing)

993
01:10:33,086 --> 01:10:36,021
You all called the police on me?

994
01:10:45,165 --> 01:10:47,065
Afternoon, Sheriff.

995
01:10:47,800 --> 01:10:50,065
Can I get you anything?
Iced tea? Lemonade?

996
01:10:50,103 --> 01:10:52,264
No, thank you, Susie.

997
01:10:52,306 --> 01:10:55,207
And don't worry,
I'm not here for you this time.

998
01:10:55,242 --> 01:10:58,439
Darden, I'm here for you.

999
01:10:58,478 --> 01:11:01,038
(sighs)
I need you to come with me.

1000
01:11:01,080 --> 01:11:03,413
I need to have a little chat with you
down at the station.

1001
01:11:03,450 --> 01:11:06,248
John, what's this all about?

1002
01:11:07,487 --> 01:11:09,819
Your buddy Jeffery
told us everything.

1003
01:11:09,856 --> 01:11:11,915
I got a warrant for your arrest.

1004
01:11:11,959 --> 01:11:15,122
I don't want this to be too formal,
so if you just get in the car,

1005
01:11:15,162 --> 01:11:17,960
- ..we can make this nice and simple.
- Let me see that warrant.

1006
01:11:17,998 --> 01:11:19,556
Give me that warrant.
Give me that warrant.

1007
01:11:31,244 --> 01:11:32,643
I'm gonna need to talk to my lawyer.

1008
01:11:32,679 --> 01:11:34,271
Yeah, well,
you can talk to him downtown.

1009
01:11:34,314 --> 01:11:36,839
Get your hands off me!
I put you in office, you moron!

1010
01:11:36,883 --> 01:11:39,852
- I own you!
- Back down, Darden.

1011
01:11:39,886 --> 01:11:42,354
Don't make me do this
in front of all these nice people.

1012
01:11:42,389 --> 01:11:46,325
This is 100,000 volts,
and it will rectify your noncompliance.

1013
01:11:47,760 --> 01:11:50,321
All right. All right.

1014
01:11:50,364 --> 01:11:52,798
We'll talk down at the station.

1015
01:12:08,982 --> 01:12:11,177
You said you wanted to
get in on the prison.

1016
01:12:11,218 --> 01:12:13,618
Well, here's your chance
to get a firsthand look at it.

1017
01:12:18,358 --> 01:12:20,849
Well, that was a nice surprise.
What did he do? What happened?

1018
01:12:20,894 --> 01:12:24,421
Your girl here lost her race
because he drugged her horse.

1019
01:12:24,464 --> 01:12:25,795
He drugged my horse?

1020
01:12:25,832 --> 01:12:28,596
He bet against her and stood to win
thousands off her loss.

1021
01:12:28,635 --> 01:12:30,193
It was a scheme.

1022
01:12:30,237 --> 01:12:32,535
I'm sorry.
It's the ugly truth.

1023
01:12:34,074 --> 01:12:35,564
I told you, Aunt Susie.

1024
01:12:35,609 --> 01:12:37,372
I felt like I was driving
a different horse.

1025
01:12:37,410 --> 01:12:40,005
We're lucky all he did
was kick down a barrel.

1026
01:12:40,047 --> 01:12:42,072
It could've been much worse.

1027
01:12:43,684 --> 01:12:45,242
I'll be taking that.

1028
01:12:45,285 --> 01:12:48,049
You won't be making it to the bank
by four anyways.

1029
01:12:49,256 --> 01:12:50,951
He won't be needing that
where he's going.

1030
01:12:50,990 --> 01:12:52,959
He'll have all of his needs
taken care of for quite some time.

1031
01:12:52,993 --> 01:12:54,085
You can be sure of that.

1032
01:12:54,127 --> 01:12:57,460
So... no high-rise?

1033
01:12:58,298 --> 01:13:01,028
Nope, no high-rise.
You okay with that?

1034
01:13:01,068 --> 01:13:03,366
Oh, I am so much more
than okay with that.

1035
01:13:03,403 --> 01:13:05,598
(laughs)

1036
01:13:06,573 --> 01:13:11,010
Hey, you're the delivery guy.

1037
01:13:11,044 --> 01:13:13,512
The one who gave me my boots.
That's my beef jerky.

1038
01:13:13,547 --> 01:13:15,742
Yep.
Also reserve deputy sheriff.

1039
01:13:15,782 --> 01:13:19,218
Somebody's gotta deliver the mail just
like somebody's gotta protect this county.

1040
01:13:19,252 --> 01:13:22,380
- Guess I'm the guy for both jobs.
- Guess so.

1041
01:13:22,422 --> 01:13:25,118
By the way, you got me hooked.
There's nothing like homemade beef jerky.

1042
01:13:25,158 --> 01:13:27,422
(laughs)

1043
01:13:27,460 --> 01:13:29,486
When are you gonna show me
how to make some?

1044
01:13:29,529 --> 01:13:30,826
I don't even know you.

1045
01:13:30,864 --> 01:13:33,196
Can't just share my deepest,
darkest secret, can I?

1046
01:13:34,167 --> 01:13:36,226
Well, maybe we should
get to know each other.

1047
01:13:37,337 --> 01:13:39,965
- Yeah.
- I get off work a little later.

1048
01:13:40,006 --> 01:13:42,736
I could swing by..
I mean, if that's okay with you.

1049
01:13:42,776 --> 01:13:45,574
- That's just fine with her.
- Mom.

1050
01:13:45,612 --> 01:13:49,309
Please do come by.
I'm making my famous blackberry cobbler.

1051
01:13:49,349 --> 01:13:51,613
- We'd love to have you.
- Mom.

1052
01:13:51,650 --> 01:13:54,017
I will be here.

1053
01:13:56,089 --> 01:13:58,489
- Bye.
- Toot-a-loo, Ron.

1054
01:13:58,525 --> 01:14:00,015
- (laughs)
- Mm.

1055
01:14:00,060 --> 01:14:03,223
So what's next, Rudy? Hmm?

1056
01:14:03,263 --> 01:14:05,663
You know, I kinda like the idea

1057
01:14:05,699 --> 01:14:07,792
of breeding and selling horses.

1058
01:14:09,202 --> 01:14:11,397
You make quite the sales boy.

1059
01:14:13,573 --> 01:14:15,700
And I got a lot of
really good names for 'em, too.

1060
01:14:16,910 --> 01:14:19,435
Like, uh, Misty.

1061
01:14:19,479 --> 01:14:21,777
Or Shadow.

1062
01:14:21,815 --> 01:14:23,806
Or Charming.

1063
01:14:24,718 --> 01:14:26,379
Rooty Tooty Fresh 'N Fruity.

1064
01:14:26,419 --> 01:14:28,046
(both laugh)

1065
01:14:28,088 --> 01:14:29,612
Hey, I love you.

1066
01:14:29,656 --> 01:14:31,351
I love you so much.

1067
01:14:31,390 --> 01:14:33,655
And I am so happy
that you're back with us.

1068
01:14:38,165 --> 01:14:39,757
Let's get going.

1069
01:14:45,939 --> 01:14:47,930
(music playing)

1070
01:15:07,727 --> 01:15:09,422
Hey, pretty lady.

1071
01:15:11,832 --> 01:15:14,858
I'm sorry about
all the trouble I caused.

1072
01:15:15,902 --> 01:15:17,836
I wanna thank you.

1073
01:15:18,872 --> 01:15:20,669
For saving this place.

1074
01:15:20,707 --> 01:15:24,199
Thank you for what you've done
for our baby girl.

1075
01:15:24,845 --> 01:15:27,143
You gave her her confidence back.

1076
01:15:27,180 --> 01:15:30,149
And she might not have won
this time out,

1077
01:15:30,183 --> 01:15:32,549
but she'll be ready
for the next time.

1078
01:15:33,887 --> 01:15:35,912
It's all coming together.

1079
01:15:36,656 --> 01:15:38,590
Y'all just keep moving.

1080
01:15:39,559 --> 01:15:41,891
We will.

1081
01:15:41,928 --> 01:15:43,919
They miss you.

1082
01:15:46,032 --> 01:15:48,091
I miss you.

1083
01:15:58,510 --> 01:16:00,945
(laughter)

1084
01:16:00,980 --> 01:16:03,745
What, you too old
to let your Aunt Sue feed ya?

1085
01:16:03,783 --> 01:16:06,308
Yes, he is.

1086
01:16:06,353 --> 01:16:09,584
- I'm gonna get you.
- Stop embarrassing him.

1087
01:16:10,357 --> 01:16:12,552
Well, everyone,
it has been a heck of a year,

1088
01:16:12,592 --> 01:16:13,957
but we made it through.

1089
01:16:13,994 --> 01:16:16,861
So glad that y'all could join us here
for his birthday.

1090
01:16:16,897 --> 01:16:19,457
I love everyone
at this table so much.

1091
01:16:19,499 --> 01:16:21,228
Happy birthday, Rudy.

1092
01:16:22,402 --> 01:16:24,131
Susie:
Happy birthday.

1093
01:16:27,607 --> 01:16:29,598
- Anne: Oh, my gosh.
- (laughing)

1094
01:16:43,490 --> 01:16:46,584
I love you all very much.

1095
01:16:47,127 --> 01:16:50,528
I'm real proud of who you are
and who I see you becoming.

1096
01:16:51,765 --> 01:16:53,824
Can't wait to ride with you again, Han.

1097
01:16:53,867 --> 01:16:57,098
One of my favorite things
in the world to do.

1098
01:16:57,137 --> 01:16:59,332
I'm excited to ride again
with you, too, Dad.

1099
01:17:02,375 --> 01:17:04,809
I love you, honey.

1100
01:17:04,844 --> 01:17:07,005
I love you more. Always.

1101
01:17:08,949 --> 01:17:10,974
I'm always here.

1102
01:17:11,017 --> 01:17:13,178
Always.

